Veronica M. Hagen: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 5:04 AM ET
Metals and Mining

Company Overview of Newmont Mining Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Veronica M. Hagen  Independent Director, Newmont Mining CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships71$312,000
Background

		Ms. Veronica M. Hagen, also known as Ronee, has been an Executive with Aluminum Company of America since 1998. Ms. Hagen served as the Chief Executive Officer of Polymer Group, Inc. from April 23, 2007 to June 18, 2013 and as its President from January 28, 2011 to June 18, 2013. Ms. Hagen has over 20 years of executive sales experience in the metals industry and has 35 years of executive experience in global operational management and commercial business leadership. ... She served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Sappi Fine Paper North America Inc. (also known as Sappi North America) from November 2004 to April 30, 2007. She served as the Chief Customer Officer of Alcoa, Inc. from June 26, 2003 to 2004. She served as Vice President of Alcoa since 2000 and is based in Chicago. Ms. Hagen served as President of Alcoa Engineered Products, Chicago, Illinois from 2000 to 2003. She served as an Executive Vice President for the Engineered Products Business at Alcoa and President for the Engineered Products from 2001 to 2003. She served as an Executive Vice President of Distribution & Industrial Products for Alumax, Inc., Cressona, Pennsylvania (formerly Cressona Aluminum Company) from 1996 to 1998. She served as Vice President of Alcoa North American Extrusions from 2001 to 2003. Prior to her affiliation with Alcoa and Alumax, She served as President of Metal Sales Associates. She served as Lead Independent Director of The Southern Company from May 2014 to May 25, 2016 and its Independent Director since December 2008. She has been a Director of AVINTIV Inc. since April 2007. She has been an Independent Director of Newmont Mining Corporation since October 31, 2005 and also Newmont Mining Corp. of Canada Ltd. since October 26, 2005. She has been an Independent Director of American Water Works Company, Inc. since February 25, 2016. She has been a Director of AVINTIV Specialty Materials Inc. (formerly Polymer Group Inc.) from April 23, 2007. She served as a Director of Rexnord-Zurn Holdings, Inc. since February 2004 and Covanta Energy, LLC (formerly Covanta Energy Corporation) since 2001. She is also a Member of a number of organizations, including The Committee of 200, the Chicago Network, Women Corporate Directors and National Association of Corporate Directors. She is a past member of the boards of the Boston Ballet, the Lyric Opera of Chicago and the Economic Clubs of Chicago and Charlotte. Ms. Hagen holds a BS/BA in International Relations from the University of Southern California and participated in an Executive Education program in Finance from the Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania and an Executive Leadership program at Harvard University.Read Full Background




